query.result:
130 I have brought you here with skill and with art;
131 now take your pleasure as your guide;
132 you are beyond the steep ways, you are beyond art.

133 See the sun that shines on your forehead;
134 see the grass, the flowers and the shrubs
135 that the earth here produces all by itself.

139 Do not wait for me to say more or give you a sign;
140 your free will is upright and sound,
141 and it would be wrong not to act as it pleases:
